
@startuml

class House {
  - address: String
  - buildingMaterial: String
  - hasBasement: Boolean
  - basement: Basement
}

class Basement {
  - type: String
  - name: String
  - size: String
  - humidityLevel: Integer (only for EarthBasement)
}

abstract class EarthBasement {
  - humidityLevel: Integer
}

abstract class ConcreteBasement {
}

class EarthBasementImpl implements EarthBasement {
}

class ConcreteBasementImpl implements ConcreteBasement {
}

class SemiDetachedHouse extends House {
  - hasOwnGarden: Boolean
  - numberOfWindows: Integer
  - hasCarportsOrGarage: Boolean
  - carports: Carport
  - garage: Garage
}

class Carport {
  - isDoubleCarport: Boolean
  - hasFlatRoof: Boolean
}

class Garage {
  - hasAutomaticDoor: Boolean
}

class Company {
  - name: String
  - address: String
}

class JobLog {
  - house: House
  - company: Company
  - hours: Integer
  - price: Double
}

House --|> Basement : has
Basement <|-- EarthBasementImpl
Basement <|-- ConcreteBasementImpl
SemiDetachedHouse --|> House
House -- Company : serviced by
House -- JobLog : has job log
Company -- JobLog : performs job
JobLog -- House
JobLog -- Company

@enduml

### Explanation:
- `House` is the base class with common attributes.
- `Basement` is an abstract class with subtypes `EarthBasement` and `ConcreteBasement`.
- `SemiDetachedHouse` is a subclass of `House` with additional properties.
- `Carport` and `Garage` are used to represent different types of parking facilities.
- `Company` represents the service companies.
- `JobLog` records jobs performed by companies on houses.

